  "texts": [
    "The intuition behind this is that LLMs are trained to predict the next word or phrase in a sequence based on the words that came before it.",
    "Through this process, the model picks up on statistical regularities and semantic associations present in the language.",
    "In essence, LLMs indirectly learn commonsense knowledge by capturing these associations and patterns from real-world usage, enabling them to make inferences about everyday concepts and situations.",
    "This is why they can generate responses that seem to reflect commonsense reasoning, even though they do not have direct access to explicit knowledge or reasoning processes.",
    "Fig. 2 An overview of our proposed TIP framework."
  ],
